But they neither came in that term, nor sent persons who should conduct their cause in our presence; thou, however, brother Urban, in the appointed term, didst present thyself in our sight ready with witnesses; and we, having for some time waited for those who were invi- ted, took the oaths of six witnesses, two of whom, that is, a certain intelligent priest, and a layman, swore that thy portion, respecting which the lawsuit had been instituted, that is, Gower, Kidwelly, Cantrebychan, Ystradyw, and Ergyng, was contained within the bounds of the diocese
